   <head>OF THE
Author.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">B</seg>ASILIVS
the Author of
this Treatise,
(vvho calleth
himselfe King
of the Romans, as their man<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ner
vvas) succeeded Michael
in the Easterne Empire; and
is sayd to haue restored the
state of the Empire, vvhich
vvas much decayed by the ill
<pb facs="4"/>
gouernment of Michael. He
raigned vvith Michael one
yeare, and after him nine<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>teene.
He dyed in the yeare
889.</p>
